summary: An Ordinance granting to The Seattle Electric Company, its successors and assigns, the right, under certain conditions, to discontinue the operation upon and to remove its tracks from the portion of route sixteen of Ordinance No. 5874 of the City of Seattle, entitled "An Ordinance granting to J. D. Lowman and Jacob Furth, their successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate street railways in the City of Seattle", approved March 9, 1900.
